## 1. Application Overview

### Purpose

ArtMind is a Progressive Web Application (PWA) that helps artists maintain consistent creative practice. It addresses documented challenges artists face: art block, burnout, and difficulty maintaining routines. Unlike tools that handle art education *or* wellbeing in isolation, ArtMind integrates both into a single platform.

### Target Users

- Art students enrolled in formal programmes
- Self-taught digital artists building independent portfolios
- Creative hobbyists seeking structured routine scaffolding

### Core Features

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Dashboard** | Personalised greeting, daily AI-generated prompt, login streak tracker, mood summary, quick-action navigation |
| **AI Inspiration Generator** | On-demand creative prompts powered by Google Gemini via Lovable AI Gateway. Supports simple (dashboard) and structured (category + difficulty) modes with warm-up, study, and challenge tiers |
| **Challenges System** | Community art challenges with creation, likes, bookmarks, comments, participation tracking, cover images, tagging, and seasonal filtering |
| **Learning Resources** | Curated, searchable library of external art learning content (videos, articles, courses) with category and type filters |
| **Habit Tracker** | Custom habit creation, daily completion logging, automatic streak calculation with backwards counting, edit/delete flows |
| **Mood Tracking** | Daily mood check-ins on a 1–5 scale with optional text notes, activity calendar heatmap, trend line chart, and weekly averages |
| **Profile System** | Display name editing, avatar upload to cloud storage, per-user settings, and authenticated session management |

### Academic Context

Developed as a BSc (Hons) Business Information Systems final-year capstone project at Westminster International University in Tashkent (WIUT). Aligned with SDGs 3 (Health & Well-being), 8 (Decent Work), 9 (Innovation), and 17 (Partnerships).

